'''Pape Alassane Gueye''' (born 24 January 1999) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] for {{Spanish football updater|Villarreal}} club [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Senegal national football team|Senegal national team]].

== Club career ==
=== Le Havre ===
Gueye made his professional debut for [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]] in a 0–0 [[Ligue 2]] tie with [[Chamois Niortais F.C.|Chamois Niortais]] on 5 May 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lfp.fr/ligue2/feuille_match/82529|title=LFP.fr - Ligue de Football Professionnel - Domino's Ligue 2 - Saison 2016/2017 - 36ème journée - Havre AC / Chamois Niortais|website=www.lfp.fr|access-date=18 December 2017|archive-date=29 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129201529/https://www.lfp.fr/ligue2/feuille_match/82529|url-status=live}}</ref> He signed his first professional contract on 20 June 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://maligue2.fr/2017/06/20/havre-premier-contrat-pro-pape-gueye/|title=Le Havre : premier contrat pro pour Pape Gueye - MaLigue2|date=20 June 2017|publisher=|access-date=18 December 2017|archive-date=4 December 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241204234304/https://maligue2.fr/2017/06/20/havre-premier-contrat-pro-pape-gueye/|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Watford ===
On 29 April 2020, it was revealed that Gueye had agreed to join Premier League team Watford when his contract with Le Havre expired on 1 July 2020. Gueye signed a five-year contract with Watford and wore the club's jersey, according to promotional material and a press release made by the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.watfordfc.com/news/club/official-hornets-sign-gueye|title=Official: Hornets Sign Gueye|publisher=Watford FC|date=29 April 2020|accessdate=30 April 2020|archive-date=5 June 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220605235929/https://www.watfordfc.com/news/club/official-hornets-sign-gueye|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|agency=Reuters|title=Marseille receives one-year transfer ban over Gueye dispute - Watford|url=https://sportstar.thehindu.com/football/marseille-one-year-transfer-ban-over-pape-gueye-dispute-watford-senegal-fifa/article38285617.ece|access-date=27 January 2022|website=Sportstar|date=18 January 2022|language=en|archive-date=26 May 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220526212810/https://sportstar.thehindu.com/football/marseille-one-year-transfer-ban-over-pape-gueye-dispute-watford-senegal-fifa/article38285617.ece|url-status=live}}</ref> Twenty-four hours later, Watford agreed a deal for Gueye's transfer to [[Ligue 1]] club [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]], which included a sell-on clause for Watford. Gueye claimed his agent had given “bad advice”, citing his Watford contract contained a salary of £45,000 per month, not the £45,000 per week that Gueye was originally quoted by his agent.<ref>{{cite news |first=Adam |last=Leventhal |title=Exclusive: Pape Gueye pictured 'signing' for Watford — but now unlikely to join |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/1899937/2020/06/30/exclusive-pape-gueye-watford-marseille-transfer/ |work=The Athletic |publisher=The Athletic Media Company |date=30 June 2020 |access-date=1 July 2020 |url-access=subscription |archive-date=7 August 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250807133611/https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/1899937/2020/06/30/exclusive-pape-gueye-watford-marseille-transfer/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Marseille handed transfer ban in Pape Gueye dispute|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/marseille-handed-transfer-ban-pape-122835324.html|access-date=27 January 2022|website=sports.yahoo.com|language=en-US|archive-date=27 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220127150529/https://sports.yahoo.com/marseille-handed-transfer-ban-pape-122835324.html|url-status=dead}}</ref>

=== Marseille ===
On 1 July 2020, Gueye signed a four-year deal with [[Ligue 1]] side [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]],<ref>{{cite press release|title=Pape Gueye est Olympien|access-date=14 September 2020|publisher=Olympique de Marseille|date=1 July 2020|url=https://www.om.fr/fr/video/4803/equipe-pro/36196-pape-gueye-est-olympien|language=fr|archive-date=6 October 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20251006040017/https://www.om.fr/fr/video/4803/equipe-pro/36196-pape-gueye-est-olympien|url-status=live}}</ref> for a reported fee of €3 million (£2.7 million).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Transferts-pape-gueye-a-l-om-officiel/1148755|title=Transferts : Pape Gueye à l'OM (officiel)|date=1 July 2020|website=[[L'Équipe]]|access-date=1 July 2020|archive-date=25 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220125044713/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Transferts-pape-gueye-a-l-om-officiel/1148755|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Walters|first=Mike|date=2 July 2020|title=Watford sell Pape Gueye to Marseille just 17 hours after finalising arrival|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/watford-sell-pape-gueye-marseille-22287414|publisher=[[Daily Mirror]]|access-date=14 July 2020|archive-date=15 August 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250815053427/https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/watford-sell-pape-gueye-marseille-22287414|url-status=live}}</ref>

==== Loan to Sevilla ====
On 30 January 2023, Gueye was loaned out to [[La Liga]] club [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] for the remainder of the season.<ref>{{cite press release|title=Pape Gueye prêté au FC Séville|access-date=30 January 2023|publisher=Olympique de Marseille|date=30 January 2023|url=https://www.om.fr/fr/actualites/4803/equipe-pro/72613-pape-gueye-prete-au-fc-seville|language=fr|archive-date=30 April 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250430172319/https://www.om.fr/fr/actualites/4803/equipe-pro/72613-pape-gueye-prete-au-fc-seville|url-status=live}}</ref> He was cup-tied for Sevilla's victorious [[2022–23 UEFA Europa League]] campaign.<ref>{{cite news
