}}</ref>

=== Villarreal ===
On 5 July 2024, Gueye joined La Liga club [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]] on a free transfer for a four-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://villarrealcf.es/pape-gueye-ya-es-groguet/|title=¡Pape Gueye ya es groguet!|trans-title=Pape Gueye is a Yellow!|language=Spanish|website=villarrealcf.es|date=5 July 2024|accessdate=5 July 2024|archive-date=16 October 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20251016215204/https://villarrealcf.es/pape-gueye-ya-es-groguet/|url-status=live}}</ref>

== International career ==
[[File:Football - 2023 Africa Cup of Nations - Finals - Guinea v Senegal - Charles Konan Stadium - Yamoussoukro - Cote dIvoire - 53483552243 (cropped).jpg|thumb|Gueye playing in the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]].]]
Gueye was born in France and is [[Senegalese nationality law|Senegalese]] by descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dakaractu.com/Le-Havre-Pape-Gueye-signe-son-premier-contrat-professionnel_a133567.html|title=Le Havre Pape Gueye sign son premier contrat professionnel - Dakar Actu|date=20 June 2017|publisher=|access-date=18 December 2017|archive-date=5 December 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241205000258/https://www.dakaractu.com/Le-Havre-Pape-Gueye-signe-son-premier-contrat-professionnel_a133567.html|url-status=live}}</ref> He represented both the [[France national under-18 football team]] and the [[France national under-19 football team|France U19s]]. However, he decided to represent Senegal on senior level. He debuted with the [[Senegal national football team|Senegal national team]] in a 2–0 [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]] win over [[Congo national football team|Congo]] on 14 November 2021.<ref name="Global Sports Archive 2021">{{cite web | title=Match Report of Senegal vs Congo - 2021-11-14 - WC Qualification | website=Global Sports Archive | date=14 November 2021 | url=https://globalsportsarchive.com/match/soccer/2021-11-14/senegal-vs-congo/2358612/ | access-date=15 November 2021 | archive-date=12 August 2025 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250812222017/https://globalsportsarchive.com/match/soccer/2021-11-14/senegal-vs-congo/2358612/ | url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Pape Gueye Stats|url=https://fbref.com/en/players/7155e3e1/Pape-Gueye|access-date=27 January 2022|website=FBref.com|language=en|archive-date=19 December 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20251219132320/https://fbref.com/en/players/7155e3e1/Pape-Gueye|url-status=live}}</ref>

He was part of [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations squads#Senegal|Senegal's squad]] for the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations]]; the Lions of Teranga went on to win the tournament for the first time in their history.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/total-africa-cup-of-nations/news/cisse-unveils-senegal-squad-hopes-for-elusive-totalenergies-afcon-title|title=Cisse unveils Senegal squad, hopes for elusive TotalEnergies AFCON title|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=25 December 2021|access-date=28 March 2023|archive-date=9 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220109145849/https://www.cafonline.com/total-africa-cup-of-nations/news/cisse-unveils-senegal-squad-hopes-for-elusive-totalenergies-afcon-title|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Senegal 0-0 Egypt |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/60186276 |website=[[BBC Sport]] |access-date=28 March 2023 |date=7 February 2022 |archive-date=23 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220723064548/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/60186276 |url-status=live }}</ref>

Gueye was appointed a [[National Order of the Lion|Grand Officer of the National Order of the Lion]] by [[President of Senegal]] [[Macky Sall]] following the nation's victory at the tournament.<ref name= "reuters">{{cite web |title=Cash prizes, real estate, and highest honours as Senegal celebrates Nations Cup heroes |url=https://www.reuters.com/lifestyle/sports/cash-prizes-real-estate-highest-honours-senegal-celebrates-nations-cup-heroes-2022-02-08/ |website=[[Reuters]] |access-date=28 March 2023 |date=8 February 2022 |archive-date=28 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230328160727/https://www.reuters.com/lifestyle/sports/cash-prizes-real-estate-highest-honours-senegal-celebrates-nations-cup-heroes-2022-02-08/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Gueye played in three of Senegal's four matches at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], starting the 2–1 win over [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]] that qualified the nation for the round of 16 for the first time since its debut in [[2002 FIFA World Cup|2002]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/team/squad/_/id/654/league/FIFA.WORLD|title=Senegal Squad|access-date=1 January 2024|website=ESPN UK|archive-date=29 December 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231229150651/https://www.espn.co.uk/football/team/squad/_/id/654/league/FIFA.WORLD|url-status=live}}</ref> In December 2023, he was named in Senegal's squad for the postponed [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]] held in the [[Ivory Coast]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/africa/67840713|title=Afcon 2023: Senegal and Sadio Mane set for defence of title|date=29 December 2023|access-date=1 January 2024|work=BBC Sport Africa|archive-date=29 December 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231229122811/https://www.bbc.com/sport/africa/67840713|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 18 January 2026, Gueye scored the winning goal for Senegal in a 1–0 victory against [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] in extra time, leading Senegal to win the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations final]], however, the match was later deemed forfeited by Senegal and the victory was awarded to Morocco on the 18th of March 2026, due to the Senegalese team walking off the pitch in protest during the match prior to Gueye's winning goal.{{Citation needed|date=May 2026}}

== Style of play ==
Gueye is a [[Midfielder#Box-to-box midfielder|box-to-box midfielder]], noted for his aggressive and highly competitive style of play. He also has a good game viewing and physical strength.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.numero-diez.com/milan-udinese-pape-gueye-calciomercato/|title=ESCLUSIVA - Milan e Udinese si muovono per un talento della Ligue 2|last=|first=|date=7 February 2020|website=Numero Diez|language=it|access-date=3 March 2020|archive-date=5 December 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201205223325/https://www.numero-diez.com/milan-udinese-pape-gueye-calciomercato/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

